[{},{"attrs":{"title":"Host and Port","description":"How to edit host and port with Nuxt.js?"},"body":"<h1><a id=\"how-to-edit-host-and-port-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#how-to-edit-host-and-port-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>How to edit host and port?</h1><p>By default, Nuxt development server host is <code>localhost</code> (only accessible from within the host machine).</p>\n<p>Host <code>0.0.0.0</code> is designated to tell Nuxt to resolve a host address, which is accessible to connections <em>outside</em> of the host machine (e.g. LAN).</p>\n<p>You can configure the connection variables in different ways.  They are listed <strong>from highest to lowest priority</strong>.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If <code>port</code> is assigned the string value of <code>&#39;0&#39;</code> (not <code>0</code>, which is falsy), a random port will be assigned to your Nuxt application.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><a id=\"as-direct-arguments\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#as-direct-arguments\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>As direct arguments</h2><pre><code class=\"hljs sh\">nuxt --hostname myhost --port 3333</code></pre><p>Or</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-string\">\"scripts\"</span>: {\n  <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"dev\"</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"nuxt --hostname myhost --port 3333\"</span>\n}</code></pre><h2><a id=\"configure-in-code-nuxt-config-js-code-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#configure-in-code-nuxt-config-js-code-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Configure in <code>nuxt.config.js</code>:</h2><p>Inside your <code>nuxt.config.js</code>:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">default</span> {\n  <span class=\"hljs-attr\">server</span>: {\n    <span class=\"hljs-attr\">port</span>: <span class=\"hljs-number\">8000</span>, <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// default: 3000</span>\n    host: <span class=\"hljs-string\">'0.0.0.0'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// default: localhost</span>\n  },\n  <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// other configs</span>\n}</code></pre><h2><a id=\"with-nuxt_host-and-nuxt_port-env-variables\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#with-nuxt_host-and-nuxt_port-env-variables\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>With NUXT_HOST and NUXT_PORT env variables</h2><p>Similar to HOST and PORT but more specific in case you need those for something else.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-string\">\"scripts\"</span>: {\n  <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"dev\"</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"NUXT_HOST=0.0.0.0 NUXT_PORT=3333 nuxt\"</span>\n}</code></pre><p><strong>Note</strong>: for better cross platform development support you can use <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/cross-env\">cross-env</a> package.</p>\n<p>Installation:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs bash\">npm install --save-dev cross-env</code></pre><pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-string\">\"scripts\"</span>: {\n  <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"dev\"</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"cross-env NUXT_HOST=0.0.0.0 NUXT_PORT=3333 nuxt\"</span>\n}</code></pre><h2><a id=\"with-host-and-port-env-variables\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#with-host-and-port-env-variables\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>With HOST and PORT env variables</h2><pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-string\">\"scripts\"</span>: {\n  <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"dev\"</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"HOST=0.0.0.0 PORT=3333 nuxt\"</span>\n}</code></pre><h2><a id=\"via-a-code-nuxt-code-config-in-the-code-package-json-code-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#via-a-code-nuxt-code-config-in-the-code-package-json-code-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Via a <code>nuxt</code> config in the <code>package.json</code>:</h2><p>Inside your <code>package.json</code>:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs json\">\"config\": {\n  \"nuxt\": {\n    \"host\": \"0.0.0.0\",\n    \"port\": \"3333\"\n  }\n},\n\"scripts\": {\n  \"dev\": \"nuxt\"\n}</code></pre>","docLink":"https://github.com/nuxt/docs/blob/master/en/faq/host-port.md"}]